# No Unnecessary Feature Descriptions

Do not add helper text, hints, or meta-descriptions that explain how a feature works unless the user explicitly asks for it.

## Avoid

- Instructional captions under interactive UI (e.g. "Swipe to explore", "Use arrows to navigate", "Auto-rotates")
- Redundant labels that restate obvious behavior
- Footer/helper lines that describe hover, tap, scroll, or keyboard affordances
- Placeholder "how to use this" copy added by default when shipping a feature

## Prefer

- Let the UI speak for itself through clear layout, icons, and interaction design
- Use `aria-label` / visually hidden text for accessibility when a control needs a name — not visible instructional paragraphs
- Add visible helper copy only when the user requests it, or when it is required for compliance, errors, or non-obvious workflows

## Examples

```tsx
// ❌ BAD — unnecessary feature description
<Carousel />
<p className="text-xs text-white/40">
  Swipe or use arrows to explore · Auto-rotates · Hover or tap to read more
</p>

// ✅ GOOD — carousel only; controls and motion are self-evident
<Carousel />
```

```tsx
// ❌ BAD
<button>Submit</button>
<span>Click submit to send the form</span>

// ✅ GOOD
<button type="submit">Submit</button>
```
